# Flutter TV App — Feature Parity with Web

Bring tv_app Flutter to match mosque_tv_web features.

## Gap Analysis

| Feature | Web ✅ | Flutter ❌ |
|---|---|---|
| **Register Account** (create new mosque + tenant) | ✅ `registerAccount()` in SyncService.js | ❌ Missing |
| **Link Account** (login with user/mobile/email + password) | ✅ `linkAccount()` in SyncService.js | ❌ Missing |
| **Disconnect Account** | ✅ `disconnectAccount()` | ❌ Missing |
| **Push config to cloud** on save | ✅ `pushConfigToCloud()` | ❌ Missing |
| **Realtime Supabase subscription** | ✅ channel subscription | ❌ Missing |
| **Settings UI** (tabbed panel in-app) | ✅ SettingsOverlay.jsx | ❌ Missing (only HTTP admin server) |
| **Slideshow panel** with modes (full/split/corner/overlay) | ✅ SlideshowPanel + TvDisplay logic | ❌ Missing — Flutter shows nothing |
| **Slideshow display modes** (full_screen, split_screen, corner_overlay) | ✅ | ❌ |
| **Ticker bar** with announcements from DB | ✅ scrolling text | ⚠️ Static hardcoded text |
| **Adhan overlay** (dismissible modes) | ✅ | ⚠️ Basic only |
| **Settings PIN protection** | ✅ keypad dialog | ❌ Missing |
| **Device ID generation** (UUID on first launch) | ✅ | ⚠️ Hardcoded `DEFAULT_DEVICE_ID` |
| **overlay_corner / overlay_size_percent** in slideshow_settings | ✅ | ❌ DB schema missing these columns |
| **sync_meta: linked_username/mobile/email** columns | ✅ | ❌ DB schema missing |

## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Slideshow images: Web stores base64 DataURL. Flutter app is Android/Windows/Linux native. Should we store base64 in SQLite (same as web) or use file paths? Base64 easiest for cross-device sync. Me recommend keep base64 (consistent with cloud sync).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Flutter Settings UI: The current `admin_server.dart` serves an HTTP panel. Web has a full in-app overlay. Should the new settings overlay REPLACE the HTTP server, or ADD alongside it? Me recommend: add Flutter in-app overlay (same as web), keep HTTP server for remote access.

